m (approx. 580 g) over pastry case and transfer onto a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm). Weave or place pastry strips in a lattice pattern over tart, pressing edges to seal. Re-roll any pastry off-cuts, if needed. Trim pastry edges and bake for 45-50 minutes (160°C), or until pastry is golden brown and jam is bubbly. Set aside to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Berry chia jam","content":["250 g strawberries, hulled","250 g raspberries","70 g raw sugar","1 ¼ tsp agar agar powder","3 tsp white chia seeds"]},{"title":"Linzer torte","content":["120 g butter, chilled and cut into pieces (3 cm), plus extra for greasing","100 g hazelnuts","100 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","100 g wholemeal spelt flour","¾ tsp baking powder","2 tbsp brown sugar (see Tips)","½ tsp ground cinnamon","¼ tsp ground cloves","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","1 egg","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 - 3 tsp cold water"]}],"id":"r126435","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-4r8NSQ6fwt8\/XZWqc4SzfNI\/AAAAAAAAfYE\/3jUPxZCzKAkSF-BmVMO9ukY7SllTNhQMwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LYJ6Yl7RTnjSU9sQ.png","title":"Linzer torte","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.4 g","fat":"15.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"22.4 g","calories":"1084 kJ \/ 258 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable sterilised jar, round fluted tart tin (23 cm), plastic wrap, silicone bread mat, baking paper, rolling pin, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If you prefer you can use any type of jam, but the Berry chia jam has much less sugar than conventional jams.","You can use your preferred brown sugar in this recipe – either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","5h 10m","12 portions"]}